# NOVA Store ‚Äî Complete Guide
## Analytics ¬∑ Future Improvements ¬∑ GitHub + Vercel Deployment

---

## PART 1 ‚Äî Analytics (Feature #20)

### What we built

`Analytics.js` is a **drop-in tracker** that sits silently on top of all your existing code. It intercepts your store's functions and fires events automatically ‚Äî you don't have to touch Cart.js, Modal.js, or anything else.

**Events tracked:**

| Event | When it fires |
|---|---|
| `page_view` | Every time the page loads |
| `view_item` | When a product modal is opened |
| `add_to_cart` | Modal "Add to Cart" button OR quick-add card button |
| `remove_from_cart` | Trash/remove in cart panel |
| `begin_checkout` | "Proceed to Checkout" click |
| `purchase` | Order placed successfully |
| `wishlist_add` | Heart button ‚Üí add |
| `wishlist_remove` | Heart button ‚Üí remove |
| `search` | Search bar (fires 0.8s after user stops typing) |
| `filter_apply` | Category pill / nav tab click |

Supports **Google Analytics 4** and **Plausible** at the same time ‚Äî or just one.

---

### Option A ‚Äî Google Analytics 4 (Free, Google)

**Step 1 ‚Äî Create a GA4 property**
1. Go to https://analytics.google.com
2. Click **Admin** (gear icon, bottom left)
3. Click **Create Property** ‚Üí choose **Web**
4. Enter your site name (e.g. "NOVA Fashion") and URL
5. Click through until you see a screen with your **Measurement ID** ‚Äî it looks like `G-A1B2C3D4E5`

**Step 2 ‚Äî Add it to Analytics.js**

Open `Analytics.js`, find this section:

```js
ga4: {
  enabled: false,
  measurementId: 'G-XXXXXXXXXX'
},
```

Replace with:
```js
ga4: {
  enabled: true,
  measurementId: 'G-A1B2C3D4E5'   // ‚Üê your actual ID
},
```

**Step 3 ‚Äî Verify it works**
1. Open your site in a browser
2. Open DevTools ‚Üí Console tab
3. You'll see `[NOVA Analytics] EVENT: page_view` etc. in gold text
4. In Google Analytics ‚Üí **Realtime** ‚Üí you should see yourself as 1 active user
5. Once confirmed, set `debug: false` in the config

**What you can see in GA4:**
- How many people visit each day/week/month
- Which products get viewed most
- Where visitors drop off (view item ‚Üí add to cart ‚Üí checkout)
- Which country/device/browser your customers use
- How long people spend on your store

---

### Option B ‚Äî Plausible (Privacy-friendly, No cookies, GDPR)

Plausible is the better choice if your customers are in the EU or you want a clean simple dashboard. No cookie banners needed.

**Step 1 ‚Äî Create account**
1. Go to https://plausible.io (30-day free trial, then ~$9/month)
2. Sign up ‚Üí Add Site ‚Üí enter your domain (e.g. `novafashion.store`)

**Step 2 ‚Äî Add it to Analytics.js**
```js
plausible: {
  enabled: true,
  domain: 'novafashion.store'   // ‚Üê must match exactly what you typed in Plausible
},
```

**Step 3 ‚Äî Add the script tag to Index.html**

Plausible works via their CDN. The `Analytics.js` loads it dynamically, but for best reliability also paste this inside your `<head>` in Index.html:

```html
<script defer data-domain="novafashion.store" src="https://plausible.io/js/script.outbound-links.js"></script>
```

---

### How to add Analytics.js to your site

In `Index.html`, after the line with `Engagement.js`, add:

```html
<script src="Engagement.js"></script>
<script src="Analytics.js"></script>   <!-- ‚Üê add this line -->
```

It must be the **last** script ‚Äî it needs all other functions to exist first.

---

## PART 2 ‚Äî What Else Can Be Done

Here's everything remaining, ranked by impact vs effort:

### üî¥ High Impact, Easy

**1. Real product images**
Replace the Unsplash URLs in `products.js` with your actual product photos. Host them on Cloudinary (free tier) or just put them in your repo's `/images/` folder.

**2. Your WhatsApp number**
In `Index.html`, find the WhatsApp link and replace the phone number:
```html
href="https://wa.me/1234567890"  <!-- replace with your real number -->
```

**3. Your actual domain in meta tags**
In `Index.html`, replace all `https://novafashion.store/` with your real URL (you'll get this after Vercel deployment).

**4. EmailJS template fix**
Your EmailJS template ID is already set. Make sure in your EmailJS template the variable names match: `{{order_id}}`, `{{customer_name}}`, `{{customer_address}}`, `{{customer_phone}}`, `{{order_details}}`, `{{order_total}}`, `{{order_date}}`.

---

### üü° High Impact, Medium Effort

**5. Cookie / GDPR banner**
If you sell to EU customers, you need a cookie consent banner before loading GA4. A simple one can be built in ~50 lines.

**6. Product image hosting**
Move images off Unsplash (which can be slow and change URLs) to Cloudinary or Vercel's image optimization.

**7. Quantity controls in cart**
Currently users can only add more items by going back to the product. Add +/- buttons directly in the cart panel.

**8. Order history page**
Save completed orders to `localStorage` so customers can see their past orders even without an account.

**9. Facebook Pixel**
If you run Facebook/Instagram ads, add the Meta Pixel alongside GA4. Same pattern as Analytics.js ‚Äî 10 lines of code.

**10. Size chart images**
The size guide popup currently shows text only. Add a real measurement chart image per category (Shoes, Leggings, T-Shirts).

---

### üü¢ Lower Priority

**11. Product reviews form**
Currently reviews are hardcoded. Build a simple form that saves to a free service like Supabase or Airtable.

**12. Stock management**
Right now stock numbers are static in `products.js`. Connect to a Google Sheet via API to manage stock without touching code.

**13. Instagram feed section**
Embed your Instagram grid at the bottom using a free widget like SnapWidget.

**14. Progressive Web App (PWA)**
Add a `manifest.json` and service worker so customers can "install" your store on their phone homescreen like an app.

---

## PART 3 ‚Äî Deploy on GitHub + Vercel

This is the full process from zero to live URL in about 15 minutes.

---

### Step 1 ‚Äî Create a GitHub account

1. Go to https://github.com
2. Sign up (free)
3. Verify your email

---

### Step 2 ‚Äî Create a new repository

1. On GitHub, click the **+** icon (top right) ‚Üí **New repository**
2. Name it: `nova-store` (or anything you like)
3. Set it to **Public**
4. Leave everything else as default
5. Click **Create repository**

---

### Step 3 ‚Äî Upload your files

Your project is a static site (no build step needed). All your files go in the root of the repo.

**Using the GitHub website (easiest):**
1. On your new repo page, click **Add file** ‚Üí **Upload files**
2. Drag and drop ALL your files:
   ```
   Index.html
   styles.css
   extras.css
   products.js
   i18n.js
   lang.js
   cart.js
   Shop.js
   Modal.js
   checkout.js
   darkTheme.js
   TrustBar.js
   Reviews.js
   InfoSections.js
   Engagement.js
   Analytics.js       ‚Üê the new file
   storage.js
   ```
3. At the bottom, click **Commit changes**

**Important:** GitHub is case-sensitive. Your `Index.html` needs to be exactly `index.html` (lowercase) ‚Äî rename it before uploading. Same for script filenames ‚Äî make sure the names in your `<script src="...">` tags match exactly (same capitalization) as the actual files.

**Quick rename checklist for Index.html script tags:**
```
index.html           (rename from Index.html)
lang.js              ‚úì
cart.js              ‚úì
Shop.js              ‚úì  (or rename to shop.js and update the tag)
Modal.js             ‚úì  (or rename to modal.js)
checkout.js          ‚úì
darkTheme.js         ‚úì  (or rename to darktheme.js)
TrustBar.js          ‚úì  (or rename to trustbar.js)
Reviews.js           ‚úì  (or rename to reviews.js)
InfoSections.js      ‚úì  (or rename to infosections.js)
Engagement.js        ‚úì  (or rename to engagement.js)
Analytics.js         ‚úì  (or rename to analytics.js)
```
The safest approach: **make all filenames lowercase** before uploading, then update the `<script src>` tags to match.

---

### Step 4 ‚Äî Deploy on Vercel

Vercel is free, instant, and gives you a real HTTPS URL.

1. Go to https://vercel.com
2. Click **Sign up** ‚Üí choose **Continue with GitHub** (uses the same account)
3. Click **Add New Project**
4. Find your `nova-store` repository ‚Üí click **Import**
5. Vercel will auto-detect it's a static site
6. Leave all settings as default
7. Click **Deploy**

In about 30 seconds, you'll see:

```
üéâ  nova-store-abc123.vercel.app
```

That's your live URL! Share it with anyone.

---

### Step 5 ‚Äî Connect a custom domain (optional)

If you want `www.novafashion.store` instead of the Vercel URL:

1. Buy a domain from Namecheap, GoDaddy, or Cloudflare (~$10‚Äì15/year)
2. In Vercel: go to your project ‚Üí **Settings** ‚Üí **Domains**
3. Type your domain ‚Üí Vercel gives you DNS records to copy
4. In your domain registrar's DNS settings, paste those records
5. Wait 5‚Äì60 minutes for DNS propagation
6. Done ‚Äî your custom domain now serves your Vercel site with free HTTPS

---

### Step 6 ‚Äî Update your site in the future

After the initial deploy, updating is just:
1. Go to your GitHub repo
2. Click the file you want to change ‚Üí pencil icon to edit
3. Make changes ‚Üí **Commit changes**
4. Vercel detects the commit and **automatically redeploys in ~20 seconds**

No manual redeployment ever needed.

---

